        <TD HEIGHT=141 COLSPAN=5>
        </TD>
        <TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH=693 HEIGHT=133 COLSPAN=3>
                    
                      <div align="left">
                      <table border="0" width="696" height="136">
                        <tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-07-03 - Corpse Update</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> <ul>
  <i>Hello all,<br>
  <br>
  I thought Id drop a line and let everyone know about some exciting changes
  that we are working on:<br>
  <br>
  First, the next EQ client will, unless a problem is discovered in testing,
  include a slash-command that will allow players to turn off display of
  corpses. This will be a client-side option that will just repress the
  rendering of the corpses themselves. This will allow corpse-related actions
  (like sense-corpse) to be taken even while corpse display is repressed.<br>
  <br>
  The command (/hidecorpses) will have three possible parameters:<br>
  <br>
  None - Shows all corpses<br>
  All - Hides all corpses but that belonging to the player.<br>
  All but group - Hides all corpses but those belonging to the player and group
  members.<br>
  <br>
  As asking people &quot;Has anyone seen my corpse?&quot; is an issue that we
  feel builds the feeling of community and encourages people to help each other
  out, the command will reset to showing all corpses upon zoning. Also, as a
  note, in its current implementation, any corpses created after the command is
  run will be shown.<br>
  <br>
  This command should help people who experience framerate problems after zoning
  in to areas known to cause a large number of corpses.<br>
  <br>
  The second change has to do with quested keys for entrance into the keyed
  dungeons on Kunark: Sebilis, Charasis, and Veeshans Peak. Its apparent that
  the risk of dying in these zones is too great to risk going with only one key.
  Furthermore, its become standard practice for people to leave a corpse at the
  entrance of these dungeons with the spare key.<br>
  <br>
  As we feel that the idea of dueling and getting killed just to leave a corpse
  for a bank isnt in the best intrest of roleplaying or our vision for the game
  (e.g. Its cheesy), weve decided to nerf this practice Our plan is to have keys
  for these three dungeons stay with the owner when they return to their bind
  point. This new ability that we are working on also gives us the opportunity
  to explore &quot;soulbound&quot; items in the future, but no promises just yet
  on that.<br>
  <br>
  -Gordon</i>
</ul>
Gordon made a second post to clear up some confusion.
<ul>
  <b><i>Judging by the responses, I apparently didnt explain it very well.<br>
  <br>
  When you die, instead of appearing at your bind point naked, youll appear
  there with your key. So yes, only one key would be needed, and thered be no
  reason to kill yourself off outside the dungeon to hold your key.<br>
  <br>
  -Gordon</i></b>
</ul>

</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='55' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> Source: EverQuest Message Board -  </font> <a href=http://http://www.everquest.com </a> http://www.everquest.com </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-07-03 - EQ Gathering Update</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> <p><font size="3">Another update from Cindy on the EverQuest Gathering taking
place in Vegas next month:</font>
<blockquote>
  <p><font size="3">As we count down the last few days open for pre-registration
  for the Las Vegas Gathering, I wanted to update people on who will be joining
  us!</font></p>
  <p><font size="3">UGO is coming!<br>
  UGO (UnderGround Online) will be joining us in Las Vegas as part of their Road
  Rave 2000 tour! They will be bringing their party van and adding to the fun!
  If you have never seen the UGO van, follow the link form our site to check it
  out!!</font></p>
  <p><font size="3">Updated list of Verant Representatives:</font></p>
