  to register to attend or for more information on the Las Vegas Gathering.</font></p>
</blockquote>
</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='55' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> Source: EQ Gathering -  </font> <a href=http://http://eqgathering.bizland.com/ </a> http://eqgathering.bizland.com/ </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-07-03 - Gordon puts out a request for help building a FAQ</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> Hello all,
<p>Id like to call on the people that are on the board here every day to help
put together questions for a FAQ. What I am looking for is questions that keep
coming up every month or so from people who are new here on the boards. I stress
that I am looking for persistent issues, rather than current issues. For
example, &quot;melee binding&quot; would be an example of a persistent issue,
where the current situation with dragons would be a current issue.
<p>I am not looking for specific class questions unless those questions are
definitely persistent in nature (e.g. Druid class-specific armor). I am
particularly not interested in those that are subjective in nature (e.g.
&quot;Why do {class} suck?&quot; &quot;suck&quot; in this case is subjective).
<p>If you all could help out in this area, Ill put some time in over the weekend
and next week putting the FAQ together. Id appreciate it if you could keep the
questions brief, cover only one issue per question, and separate them clearly in
your replies.
<p>Thanks,
<p>-Gordon<br>
</p>
